Bring a #large pot{} of water to a boil with a large pinch of @salt{pinch}. Once
boiling, add @brown rice{3/4%cup} and cook until tender, ~{25-30%minutes}. Drain
and return to pot. Keep covered until rest of meal is ready.

Wash and dry all produce. While rice cooks, peel @carrots{1}. Using a
#vegetable peeler{}, shave it into ribbons, running blade down the length.
Repeat with @zucchini{1}. Trim @scallions{2}, then thinly slice into
3-inch-long, matchstick-sized strands. Chop @baby broccoli{6%oz} into bite sized
pieces. Thinly slice @button mushrooms{4%oz}. Mince or grate @garlic{2%cloves}.
Peel and mince @ginger{1%thumb}.

In one #small bowl{}, toss scallions with @white wine vinegar{2%tbsp} and a pinch
of salt. Set aside to allow scallions to quick-pickle. In another small bowl,
stir @soy sauce{1.5%oz}, garlic, ginger, and @sugar{1%tsp} until sugar dissolves.

Heat a drizzle of @vegetable oil{1%tbsp} in a #large pan{} over medium heat.
Add carrot. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Cook until tender but still crisp,
~{4-5%minutes}, tossing frequently. Remove from pan and set aside. Add another
teaspoon oil to pan and repeat with zucchini, removing from pan once cooked.
Add baby broccoli, mushrooms, and a drizzle of oil to pan and toss until tender,
~{6-8%minutes}. Season with salt and pepper. Remove from pan and set aside.

Pour soy sauce mixture into same pan. Bring to a simmer and let cook until
slightly thickened, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Divide rice between plates. Arrange carrots, zucchini, baby broccoli, and
mushrooms on top. > TIP: If adding an egg, place it on top of veggies. Garnish
with scallions and @sesame seeds{1%tbsp}. Drizzle with sauce from pan and
@hot sauce{3%tsp}(to taste).